ries expose the grit and burden of stalled lives, the universal desire for intimacy, and a wistful realization of the off-kilter and even perverse nature of love.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aUkrainian poetryvTranslations into English. 0aUkrainian prose literaturevTranslations into English. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aCostigan-Humes, Reilly.1 aPhipps, Wanda.1 aTkacz, Virlana.1 aWheeler, Isaac Stackhouse.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311063899840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030023573940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235739423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300235739/original  a978-3-11-063899-8  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles